node.text:
Sequoia National Park 😳 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on tourfervor.com (link in my bio: @tourfervor)

Home to some of the tallest trees in the world including the General Sherman Tree, the world's largest tree, standing 275 feet tall with a base more than 36 feet in diameter. 🌲

Tag a friend you’d like to visit here with!

📽 @world.from.my.eyes
📍Squoia National Park, California

node.text:
Colorful streets of Alaurín de la Torre in Málaga 😍 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @tourfervor 

Eva Pacheco, a local crochet teacher in this town of southern Spain, used her and her students' skills to make colorful sunshades for the town. 
Southern Spain is accustomed to extreme heat in the summer season and has historically used plastic awnings to shade walkways. The City Council's Department of the Environment recently implemented a plastic-free order. 

To accommodate the eco-friendly endeavour, Pacheco and a dozen other women used recycled fabric to crochet awnings in place of the plastic. Since the Council's decision three years ago, the sunshades are rolled out each summer. This year they comprise roughly 500 square meters of recycled fabric. While they provide refuge from the sun, the sunshades also add a pop of color to the Spanish streets.
📸 @myeyesshowmepictures

node.text:
Would you dare to live this experience? 🤪 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @tourfervor.

The Pendulum Jump in Brazil is a life-changing leap that will challenge your limits. 🤯

2.5 seconds free fall over the Avencal Waterfall, a magnificient scenery that’s 100 meters high and located 10 km away from the village of Urubici, in the State of Santa Catarina. If you’re looking for a breath taking activity that brings you closer to @nature, no doubts that’s it. 🙌🏼

📽 @fragatafpv @saltodependulo

node.text:
What would your reaction be? 🤪 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @tourfervor

If you come face to face with this guy whilst diving?

Marine iguanas Marine Iguanas are the only marine lizard species in the world found only in the Galápagos Islands. They can dive as deep as 30m (98ft) and hold their breaths for 30-40 mins. It’s believed that they evolved from a common ancestor millions of years ago after arriving on the islands by rafting.

📽 @KenzoKiren
📍Galapagos Islands, Ecuador
